        zeroFront[i] = 0;
    }

As other people have already pointed out your mistake, here&#39;s another way to solve this problem using streams with the teeing collector (this was added in java 12, not sure what version of java codingbat is running):
```java
public int[] zeroFront(int[] nums) {
    return Arrays.stream(nums).boxed().collect(
            Collectors.teeing(
                    Collectors.filtering(n -&gt; n == 0, Collectors.toList()),
                    Collectors.filtering(n -&gt; n != 0, Collectors.toList()),
                    (zeros, nonZeros) -&gt; Stream.concat(zeros.stream(), nonZeros.stream())
                            .mapToInt(Integer::intValue)
                            .toArray()
            ));
}
```

